seal     : The popular picture of the atom — electrons circling a nucleus like planets — is wrong. Quantum mechanics says an electron has no definite path; it exists as a cloud of probability, an 'orbital,' a shape of where it is likely to be found. The atom is mostly empty space wrapped in fuzz. This sphere draws the honest version: stippled clouds, not rings.
